<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="368" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,759,1787,1901]" lastBlockId="8.[806,1422,1512,1901]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis box="[144,280,1788,1809]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Description:</emphasis>
Male. Head: frons black on upper part, brown on lower part. Face black on upper part, orange-brown on lower part. Thorax: scutum with black patches and silver-grey pollinose pattern. Scutellum orange-brown, black along margin. Legs: hind tibiae with three black rings; subapically with two to three rows of short, scopiform setae on ventral surfaces (
<figureCitation box="[926,1009,1603,1625]" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="5.[164,254,1159,1178]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–6. Hindlegs of male. For details of the parts denoted by letters a–e see the descriptions of individual species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687815/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
) and one very long apical seta (
<figureCitation box="[814,898,1634,1656]" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="5.[164,254,1159,1178]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–6. Hindlegs of male. For details of the parts denoted by letters a–e see the descriptions of individual species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687815/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
), lacking any long setae on ventral and posteroventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1105,1664,1687]" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="5.[164,254,1159,1178]" captionTargetBox="[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-318@5.[387,1219,194,1128]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–6. Hindlegs of male. For details of the parts denoted by letters a–e see the descriptions of individual species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687815/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). All fifth tarsomeres black, the rest grey-yellow. Male terminalia: ventral margin of epandrium not elongated (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1249,1726,1748]" captionStart="Figures 20, 21" captionStartId="8.[144,234,1400,1419]" captionTargetBox="[370,1196,796,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-207@8.[367,1199,794,1370]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 20, 21. Phortica panda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 20, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 21, hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687826/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Cercus with three strong setae (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1113,1756,1779]" captionStart="Figures 20, 21" captionStartId="8.[144,234,1400,1419]" captionTargetBox="[370,1196,796,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-207@8.[367,1199,794,1370]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 20, 21. Phortica panda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 20, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 21, hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687826/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with two prensisetae apically (
<figureCitation box="[1024,1106,1787,1809]" captionStart="Figures 20, 21" captionStartId="8.[144,234,1400,1419]" captionTargetBox="[370,1196,796,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-207@8.[367,1199,794,1370]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 20, 21. Phortica panda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 20, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 21, hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687826/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Paramere mediobasally with a triangular projection, submedially with one small process, which bears one sensillum; basal process with fine sawteeth (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1215,1879,1901]" captionStart="Figures 20, 21" captionStartId="8.[144,234,1400,1419]" captionTargetBox="[370,1196,796,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-207@8.[367,1199,794,1370]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 20, 21. Phortica panda Cao &amp; Chen sp. nov., male. 20, epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; 21, hypandrium, gonopods, paramere, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme. For abbreviations see Figs 14 and 15. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4687826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4687826/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
